<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="ie=edge">
    <title>Davids</title>

    <style>
        html {
            line-height: 1.6rem;
            font-family: -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, 'Open Sans', 'Helvetica Neue', sans-serif;
            font-size: 18px;
            background-color: #222;
        }

        body {
            max-width: 900px;
            margin: 2rem auto;
            background: #ddd;
            padding: 2rem;
        }
    </style>

</head>
<body>
    
    <h1>Davids</h1>
    <p>
        Demo <a href="https://11ty.io">Eleventy</a> application to showcase a Google Forms based static content posting system.
    </p>
    <h3>How it works</h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Post an entry using <a href="https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScjSOj7TIS-OAD-ytJBdqUb5PtF5FUBOlEJ9KWXylAdSdv8Yg/viewform">this Google Form</a></li>
        <li>This will be stored in a Google Sheet which is published as CSV to <a href="https://sheety.co">Sheety API</a> resulting in <a href="https://api.sheety.co/a802849e-6e65-4e4c-afdb-1acef4becb9a">this JSON endpoint</a> </li>
        <li>Eleventy consumes the data file and publishes it from the <code>_data</code> folder</li>
    </ol>
    <ul>
    {% for david in davids %}
    <li>{{david.name}} - b.{{david.dob}} - favourite colour = {{david.favourite_colour}}</li>
    {% endfor %}
    </ul>
</body>
</html>